{# Renders the FreeIPA CA cert into a docker-config file mounted at
   mattermost_ldap_ca_cert_path inside mm-app.

   Heads-up — Mattermost's MM_LDAPSETTINGS_PUBLICCERTIFICATEFILE is
   the mTLS *client* certificate path, not a CA-trust override. Go's
   crypto/tls only verifies LDAP server certs against the system CA
   pool. The mount itself works (verified), but Mattermost won't use
   it for trust-store purposes today. Wire this template up so that
   a future image rebuild (which drops the cert into /etc/ssl/certs
   and runs update-ca-certificates) can find it without changing the
   role. Until then, use mattermost_ldap_skip_certificate_verification
   when running against a self-signed CA.

   The cert content is slurped at deploy time from a FreeIPA server
   (mattermost_freeipa_ca_cert_src on groups['freeipa'][0]) — it's
   public, so it doesn't belong in ansible-vault. See
   roles/app_mattermost_swarm/tasks/main.yml for the slurp + b64decode. #}
